post_text:
For our October 20th fall concert, we will be having a jack-o-lantern contest instead of our 50/50 raffle.

Choir students are welcome to participate in the contest by submitting a carved, or painted pumpkin.

Tickets will be sold at the door for $1 which families can place into a jack-o-lantern jar. The winner will receive half of the proceeds, and the remaining half will go toward the music boosters for future concert costs.

Reminder that High school tenors/basses should have black dress socks, black dress shoes, white undershirt, and assigned uniform.
Soprano/altos should have black dress shoes, black socks/pantyhose, and optional undershirt.

Students grades 6-8 should have black socks, black shoes, and black undershirt.

Later details will come for times.

We look forward to a great concert!

post_text:
On Friday, March 29th, we had the pleasure of Dr. Greg Ramsdell from Heidelberg University work with the High school choir.
It was an eye-opening experience for the students!

Thank you Dr. Ramsdell!

post_text:
The choir concert has been scheduled for April 7th, at 6:00 PM.
Call time will be 5:15 PM for students.

High school students are expected to wear their white undershirts (Tenors and Basses only), black shoes, and black socks/pantyhose and their assigned dress at school.

6th and 7th-8th choirs are expected to wear black shoes, black socks/pantyhose, black undershirt, and their polo at school.

6th and 7th-8th choirs are expected to wear black shoes, black socks/pantyhose, black undershirt, and their polo at school.
